[thinking] **Evaluating GraalVM defaults**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm thinking about GraalVM defaults since JDK 21 and how classes are initialized. It seems that many classes are initialized at runtime, especially for third-party libraries, unless they're proven to be safe. If it’s runtime, reflection usually requires metadata, but I wonder if the dynamic access report can recognize those calls. GraalVM can automatically detect certain reflections and register them, but perhaps not all targets, even constants. I’m considering using the existing build cache for compilation issues.
[thinking] 
